The paper discusses the application of Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks in hydrology for rainfall-runoff forecasting. As such, it is likely to fall under the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This category covers research on the development and analysis of machine learning algorithms, which is the focus of this paper. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This category covers research on the development and analysis of intelligent agents, which can include machine learning algorithms. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): This category covers research on neural networks and other biologically-inspired computing systems, which includes LSTMs. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): This category covers research on the use of computational methods in engineering, finance, and science, which includes hydrology. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): This category covers research on social and information networks, which may be relevant if the paper discusses the use of network analysis techniques in hydrology.
